headline: Charlie Munger Warned About BlackRock's Power—'We Have A New Bunch Of Emperors,' And Larry Fink Shouldn't Rule The World
summary: Charlie Munger was honest about the growing influence of index fund managers like BlackRock’s (NYSE:BLK) Larry Fink. The late Berkshire Hathaway (NYSE:BRK, BRK.B)) vice chairman warned that passive investing has resulted in a massive shift in voting power, one that he believed could have serious consequences. We have a new bunch of emperors...maybe we can make Larry Fink and the people at Vanguard pope. That is going to change the world...it will not be good." Charlie Munger pic.twitter.com/2Fvb
